Key Match Events: Chris Woakes and Adil Rashid each took three wickets
Chris Woakes and Ben Stokes built a 129-run partnership
Post-Match Reflections: England captain Jos Buttler: 'We were desperate for the win. We got off to a great start, had a bit of a speed bump in the middle. We needed someone to stand up and take charge. There was some very smart cricket between Stokes and Woakes to get us to that score.'
Ben Stokes: 'I'm more pleased for us to get a victory over the line, it's been a tough World Cup and nice to get back to winning ways today.'
England play Pakistan on Saturday. A win would almost certainly guarantee their place at the Champions Trophy but it doesn't necessarily.
England have climbed to seventh, and as things stand would qualify for the Champions Trophy in Pakistan in 2025.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Chris Woakes has gone level with Ian Botham on 30 wickets, the joint-most for England at World Cups.
Adil Rashid has improved throughout this tournament and finished with 3-54 from eight overs, making him England's leading wicket-taker in the tournament with 13.
